Weekly Highlights 20230125-20230201

1/28-1/30 OKC Lab Outage

  • Lab outage from 1/28 to 1/30 to accommodate file server upgrade. Still backfilling data...

1/26 - AP1 GUS Faulted from Backup

1/26 06:04 - AP1 GUS faulted from Backup Mode with SEs 143 and 193 indicating C5 KPA Failure in the RFU Subsystem

  • MT: The GUS Maintainer arrived at the equipment at 06:19UTC and found the C5 KPA faulted with a Body Current Fault. He reset the fault and placed the KPA back into Transmit. A few minutes later the KPA faulted again with the same fault. The spare C5 KPA (C5A) was brought online and the system was turned over to WAAS Ops at 06:31UTC. WAAS Ops executed a Control Power Off/Restart at 06:33:20UTC. Following the restart, the GUS was placed into Maintenance and the RFU ANT/TLT baseball switches were placed into TLT position and a TLT Verification was initiated.
  • The faulted KPA was removed from the GUS C5B slot and an on-site spare unit installed to restore the GUS to full redundant capability. That spare KPA is currently up and running and will remain running for a confidence test while being monitored by the DCAF system.
  • **Restored to Backup Mode at 1/26 09:10** after multiple Control Powers and the usual Rcvr Init Fails

1/27 - YFB WRE-C Caused O&M Core Dump

YFB WRE-C was previously Control Powered OFF to avoid O&M Core Dumps due to dead time-of-day battery; however, the WRE spontaneously came back online uncommanded. This caused an extended outage for both O&Ms due to the inability to Control Power OFF YFB WRE-C while Ring 1 is down.

  • 1/27 15:22 - YFB WRE-C PCU alarms rescinded; no apparent Control Power command issued; unclear why PCU came back online...
  • 1/27 16:06 - When YFB WRE-C came up to Maintenance Mode with the bad battery, both O&Ms Core Dumped
  • Reached out to YFB to power off PCU-C, but since there's ongoing comm issues on Ring 1 and PCU-C powers the Ring 2 Access Router, the site is now frequently entering No Data Reported Mode until the PCU-C can be restored -- we can request that the technician pull AC1 and AC3 then flip the CB1 to the ON position to restore Ring 2
  • POCC O&M restored to Normal after PCU-C powered off -- 1/27 17:07
  • **No O&M Monitoring from 1/27 16:24 to 1/27 17:00 -- > 30 minute monitoring outage**

2/1 - DX1 GUS Maintenance Activities

  • 2/1 13:59 - DX1 to Maintenance to restore ACU to DX1 frequency and switch over C1 KPA to Stby KPA; **restored to Backup Mode at 2/1 15:23**; ref [LIR 407451232](https://technetrmlsb.faa.gov/LIR/Details/407451232)

ZTL Core Node Comm Issues

  • No major events since 1/5
  • FTI replaced OC48 switch on 1/1; monitoring for 30 days running clean; ends 2/4

SZ1 Ring 1 ALT / Ring 2 PRI Issues

  • 1/11 16:45 - Both circuits still flapping intermittently; flapping ended at 1/12 05:58; running much cleaner since
  • 1/25 Status - Daily flapping between 06:00 and 10:00 UTC
  • 2/1 Status - Currently cleared (apparently repaired during lab outage)

ZDV WRE-C Maintenance

  • Next action is to send NASE engineer for Time / Frequency Domain Reflectometry

YFB Ring 1 Comm Flapping Ongoing

YFB Ring 1 has experienced ongoing comm flapping issues since 8/3/2022; no ETA for repair.
